Developments and trends in welfare society and welfare approaches. Approaches to leisure. Health as defined by the World Health Organisation. Approaches to holistic well-being, well-being dimensions and energy. Personal well-being and lifestyle.Objectives/eesmärkid:  To provide knowledge and a comprehensive understanding of the development and trends of approaches to wellness and health, and the influencing factors of personal well-being.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Upon the completion of the course the student: 1) understand and be able to analyse various approaches to wellbeing; 2) know the definition of health according to the World Health Organisation and the influencing factors of health; 3) understand the principles of healthy lifestyles and holistic well-being; 4) be able to critically analyse the influences and improvement opportunities of personal well-being.
